items.name: Erina Kinjo Won - Martian Successor Nadesico
items.description:
The best or only "evil" secretary in Nadesico. My second favorite character of the series, the first being Inez Fressange and probably the only other good one is Yurika Misumaru. Getting images was a pain and ended up using mostly screencaps which i had to scrub and filter due to graininess (stupid 90s low res crap). Anyway it ended up ok-ish. SD seems to really hate lipstick for some reason.

V2:

I was a bit displeased with the V1 LORA and as I am doing some test with the prodigy optimizer I decided to do a retrain. It looks a bit better and is more stable.

Got ok results with: <lora:ErinaKinjoWonV2:.7> ErinaKinjoWon

I tweaked her outfits tagging to make them a bit more reliable the new tags are:

  • nergal_military_uniform_black_pencil_skirt_grey_thighhighs

  • erina_red_skirt_suit

V1:

Got ok results with: <lora:ErinaKinjoWon:.75> ErinaKinjoWon, large_breasts,

Available outfits are:

  • NergalUniform

  • ErinaSkirtSuit

Warning: SD seems to hate lipstick, when i find a fix i might do a V2.0. It seems unwise to use lipstick, red_lips or makeup in the NAI family models. Anyway that issue lowers the success rate of this lora. You can just say screw it and add lipstick and red_lips in the negatives to nip the issue at the bud. After doing a stupidly huge xyz(I'll add it as an extra gallery) plot I determined you can use red_lips and lipstick at no more than .55 weight combined so (red_lips:.4), (lipstick:.4) are good values to get decently looking lipstick.

Might be a good idea to add skirt, miniskirt or pencil_skirt to the outfits as sometimes it likes to give her pants(Which is not her cannon outfit.). Canonically she uses either stockings or thighhighs.

You may also want to add short_hair as in some front shoots the lora seems to like adding her long hair or a ponytail.

Her mole seems to come and go with the LORA strength. Use mole or mole_under_mouth at your own peril as the model(anythingV4.5) may go way overboard with the amount of moles.

Since this was mostly trained with screencaps(Don't want to be sued :P) i will refrain from posting the dataset, in it's place I'll add the tag summary.

IF YOU ARE NEW TO STABLE DIFFUSION OR YOU HAVE PROBLEMS WITH MY MODELS, GO HERE: Guide

IF YOU YOUR PICTURES HAVE PROBLEMS CHECK MY FAQ SECTION: FAQs

RIGHT NOW IMAGES METADATA ARE MISSING AS I'M USING COMFYUI TO SIMPLIFY THE IMAGE GENERATION. I'M TRYING TO FIND A WAY TO FIX THIS, IF SOMEONE KNOWS HOW TO DO IT, I'D LIKE TO KNOW.

What's this LoRA

This is a LoRA trained on female portraits made by Paul Rubens. My models are not trained to achieve the exact style of their source, but to change the general vibe of the image. They are also fine-tuned on anime models, so they may not work perfectly with realistic ones.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my custom):

  • https://civitai.com/models/24149

  • https://civitai.com/models/28322

You don't need to specify a word to trigger this LoRA.

The LoRA works also on NSFW (check out the examples).

Guides

Learn how to create pictures like mine with my step-by-step tutorials:

items.name: Cinderella
items.description:
Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

TLDR (Because I don't care)

Use cinderella <lora:cinderella_v10:1> in positiv promt.

If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) ;D

About

I don't know why, but I felt the need to create a Cinderella LoRa, I don't really like the story (especially from the second film, that's no story...), so I think I just did it because Cinderella is cute... Overall I would consider the model a failure, didn't work out as expected and only in some cases the model produces what I expected...

Training

I gathered 47 images from both movies, but the majority came from the first movie (I think the second movie was one of these VHS only releases so not so good images and the art style was a bit different but okay... I was able to work with it. This was my first try using tags to define different outfits, and I screwed up a bit with her "normal" outfit, see the usage section below. Eventhou it was a failure I learned quite a lot ^^

Usage

No weighing is required, so it's as simple as that:

cinderella <lora:cinderella_v10:1>

This is the first LoRa where I tried to train the different outfits of the character... so there are 4 outfits with corresponding trigger words:

medieval maid - casual/work outfit if your checkpoint knows the concept of maids (aka any anime checkpoint), add (maid:2) into your negative promt, couldn't think a better name for this outfit ...

princess dress - princess dress

ripped dress - when her original dress was ripped by her stepsisters

nightgown - from the first scene of the first movie (was only trained with 2-3 images, so it is a bit hard to get)

I think the best result I got was with dreamshaper, with any other model she didn't looked quite right (but still cute ;D)

items.name: Middle parted hair - concept
items.description:
This is a very basic LoRA. Its purpose is to add (middle) parted hair to your character.

You may be asking: why don't you just prompt it like everyone else?

The thing is, I've had difficulties in the past when using a certain seed/model/lora to get a middle parted hairstyle or without affecting composition, so I decided to try and make a lora to help solve it.

I wasn't considering releasing it but thought someone else might find it useful. This works well with many models.

You don't need a trigger word but you can increase the effect by using the standard tags for parted hair: parted hair and/or forehead.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: Nophica, The Matron (FFXIV)
items.description:
My very first LoRa. Settling with this result since the more I train and experiments, the result got worst. Also, with my outdated PC each training takes 4+ hours to finish, might be better to release it into the wild to fish for tips before experimenting more. 95% created from in-game screenshots trained against the awesome NED model.

Trigger words

  • nophica, 1woman, redhair, green eyes, green dress, leaf circlet = should work generally

  • pink pupil, leather choker, armlet = can be added but might not changing much

  • leaf thigh strap = can be used to prompt result above knees

I might have over prompt on these, thinking I had to be as detailed as I can over the datasets. Let me know if this is actually unnecessary

Recommendation

  • Clip Skip 2

  • HiRes fix at least 1.5 (Examples use Denoise 0.5 and 4k-Ultrasharp)

  • The TI's in the negative prompts used in the examples especially bad-hands-5.

  • Weight 0.6 ~ 0.8. I recommend 0.7

  • I use motherly, milf, curvy to get the momma look

Links:

  • bad-hands-5

  • bad-artist

  • EasyNegative

  • Deep Negative v1x

  • 4k-Ultrasharp

v0.5

An accidental training I did that somehow able to provide an eye appealing realistic pictures. But, in my opinion, it is more to applying 'nophica like' style to the character.

I don't even remember the training parameter for it and unable to replicate it.

Strongly recommend using 0.9 for the weight.

Tips?

Appreciate any tips/guide to get the model more tame/adaptable. Not satisfied yet with the lighting hard to tone it down and small characteristic that the AI can't get it right.

items.name: CityEdge_ToonMix
items.description:
日本語の説明は後半にあります。

This model is for producing toon-like anime images, but it is not based on toon/anime models. This model is based on the photorealistic model (v1: chilled regeneric v2, v3: Muse), and then transformed to toon-like one.

If you use my model "CityEdgeMix", you may notice that same prompt/seed as CityEdgeMix also produces similar images as CityEdge_ToonMix. CityEdge_ToonMix is based on CityEdgeMix, which is photorealistic merge model, and merged some anime/toon models with low coefficients to expand desctiption variations, and then transoformed to a toon-like model.

Both SFW and NSFW is capable. VAE is not needed but you can try some.

Note: NOT using EasyNegative will result in more various face types. EasyNegative is powerful good negative prompt, but it seems a little too strong for this model.

List of my models

  • CityEdgeMix : Simple photo-realistic model based on Chilled family

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : Simple 2.5D anime-like model based on CityEdgeMix

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : Pure 2D anime-like model merging only 2D models

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : Anime-like model with detail depiction by making use of block-merge

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 2.5D model focusing on unique depiction through merging many models and block-merge.

  • Landscape_Photoreal : Model that produces photorealistic output, whether with characters or just the background

  • CityEdge_DollyMix : Model that produces doll-like and 3D animated movie-like output

アニメ調の出力を得るためのモデルですが、アニメ系のモデルからではなく実写系のモデル（v1: chilled-regereric v2, v3:Muse）から出発し、最後にアニメ調のタッチに変換して作成したモデルです。

公開している実写系のモデル「CityEdgeMix」に、アニメ系の出力のバリエーションを持たせるためにいくつかのアニメ系モデルを軽くマージし、その後アニメ系の出力モデルに変換しています。ですので、CityEdgeMixと同じプロンプトやシード値を使うと、よく似た出力を得ることができるはずです。

エロ・非エロどちらでも可。VAEは焼き込み済ですが彩度は浅めなので別のものも試してみていいと思います。

注：EasyNegativeを使うと同じ顔ばかりになる傾向があるようです。顔のバリエーションを増やしたい場合はあえてEasyNegativeを外すと、期待する効果が得られるかもしれません。

モデル一覧

  • CityEdgeMix : Chilled系をベースにしたシンプルなフォトリアル系マージモデル

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : CityEdgeMixを2.5D化したシンプルな2.5Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : 2Dモデルだけをマージしたピュア2Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : 階層マージを駆使してディテール描写にこだわったアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 多数のモデルのマージと階層マージによる独自の描写にこだわった2.5Dモデル

  • Landscape_Photoreal : キャラクターがいても、背景だけでも、フォトリアルな出力が得られるモデル

  • CityEdge_DollyMix : ドール調・3Dアニメ映画調の出力が得られるモデル

items.name: 90s TMNT Donatello - Realistic
items.description:
Nothing I've come across so far could do convincing enough TMNT Turtles, so I took it upon myself to make a few models of my own. This is by no means perfect and it basically refuses to work on many models, probably due to the fact I trained on Experience 8.0. I'll be training on a comic/toon based model soon in hopes that I can reproduce the comic book style art as well.

Trained on about 100 HD of the 1990s style TMNT images for about 2000 steps

I recommend 512x512 or 768 and a weight of 0.8-0.9

High res fix is hit or miss, sometime it ruins it

20 - 30 steps seems to be the sweet spot, sometimes lower steps (around 20) produces better results

I recommend putting "toy" and "3D" in the negative prompt

Play around with the setting and weights and prompts and hopefully you can get something you like.

This is the initial alpha release and as such it is very much a trial and error process.

This was trained on a singular character and tested for such, so I'm not sure how it would handle groups.

Not trained for, or tested for NSFW, so be aware it may not work for NSFW.

The other Turtles are also being released as alphas at the time of writing this so be sure to check them out!

As always, if you have any tips for improving my training, please let me know! And please rate & comment & share your generations.

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

A lora based on the artist gaston 18

the training data was provided by a very helpful user!

Trained with 736 images

  • Model used kotomix

  • bad hands embedding

  • bad artist embedding

  • bad prompt embedding

  • deep negative embedding

  • Lollypop upscaler

Known Issues

  • None that I have found

Training settings?

The most important part of training is getting a good dataset!

Training settings can be found by installing the additional networks extension in auto1111

Extensions -> available -> load from -> additional networks

Restart webui

place lora into stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-additional-networks\models\lora

To view the training settings

Go to additional network tab -> choose model -> training parameters

items.name: shaosiming_少司命——秦时明月
items.description:
秦时明月少司命的LoRA模型，由于能找的的高清图片很少，训练数据集质量较差，大多是视频截图或者宣传海报图，采用国风3（guofeng3_v32.ckpt [0bb33c7041]
）模型做为底模，基于Dreambooth插件进行LoRA训练，最终训练结果在底模下权重为1时，有较高脸部识别率，使用底模时面纱有一半以上概率能出，其他模型面纱基本没有，脸部辨识度也不高，服装比较复杂，没有单独训练，所以服装还原度也不高，这是本人第一次训练模型，肯定会有很多问题，但是可以将就用一下，期待能有更好的模型。

（经本人在多个底模上进行测试，发现LoRA权重在1~1.4范围内效果较好，如果没有出现面纱，可以适当加强veil这个tag）

2.0版本模型采用秋叶的lora整合包进行训练，把原来数据源中透明背景的图片全部改为了白色背景，而且未进行统一分辨率裁剪，移动端3080显卡用整合包训练，同样数量的数据源，训练时间基本在30分钟左右，产出的包体积更小，效果更好，不再会有1.0那样模糊的效果了，与各大模型结合也更容易，不再会使整体画面偏紫色了，2.0版本lora模型权重在0.5~0.8之间效果最稳定，0.6以上时容易出面纱。

权重在0.4时，能保留模型主体特征，并提供更大的自由度以更换姿势、服装及背景，画出更通用但不那么还原的图。

初始分辨率540x960，采用R-ESRGAN 4x+放大算法，重绘幅度0.3放大2倍进行高清修复，然后图生图用SD upscale脚本，选择同样的算法，重绘幅度0.1进行超分放大，可以得到效果不错的4k高清图片。（此方法第一步直接生成1080P的图片，比较看脸，不易批量操作，16G显存最多只能同时生成4张图片，出图及修图效率较低，但是质量较高）
